SIMPLE: cheapen
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cheapen
<hw>Cheap"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Cheapened</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Cheapening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>cheapien</ets>, <ets>chepen</ets>, to trade, buy, sell, AS.
<ets>ce⟦aacute⟧pian</ets>; akin to D. <ets>koopen</ets> to buy, G.
<ets>kaufen</ets>, Icel. <ets>kaupa</ets>, Goth. <ets>kaup⟦omac⟧n</ets>
to trade. Cf. <er>Chap</er> to bargain.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To ask
the price of; to bid, bargain, or chaffer for.</def>
<mark>[Obsoles.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pretend to <qex>cheapen</qex> goods, but nothing buy.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Cf. <er>Cheap</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>To
beat down the price of; to lessen the value of; to depreciate.</def>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My proffered love has <qex>cheapened</qex> me.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cheapener</ent>⟦br⟧
